# config/osb.pin — typed OsbPin (ARCHITECTURE.md §13, §6, §8; task 13.1 anti-corruption layer)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PURPOSE
#   obsidian-second-brain (OSB) is the upstream source-extractor / retrieval
#   toolkit (upstream repo:
#   https://github.com/eugeniughelbur/obsidian-second-brain) that SoW inherits
#   FROM through an ANTI-CORRUPTION LAYER: its vault-agnostic extractor patterns
#   are re-implemented as EMIT-ONLY SourceIngestionPort adapters
#   (packages/integrations/src/connectors/adapters/*-source.ts) that produce
#   CANDIDATE data through registerSource() and NEVER write the canonical vault
#   (safety rule 1 — one writer; KnowledgeWriter is the provably-sole autonomous
#   Markdown writer, §6). SoW depends on the internal SourceIngestionPort, never
#   OSB's command surface. This pin records the upstream release the inheritance
#   tracks + a content-SHA of any vendored subtree, so a version bump is a
#   DELIBERATE act, never silent (mirrors config/gbrain.pin; the Hermes-pin
#   re-validation precedent, LESSON providers#1).
#
# ENFORCEMENT (task 13.1 gate a)
#   packages/evals/src/osb/anti-corruption-guard.ts `scanForWriteSurfaces`
#   statically scans the *-source.ts extractor family (and a future vendor/osb/**
#   tree) for FORBIDDEN write-surface tokens (@sow/knowledge sole-writer import,
#   node:fs write ops, createFsVault, atomic-vault-commit, Tool-Gateway
#   ExternalWriteEnvelope). The conformance suite asserts 0 violations AND a
#   count-pinned scannedCount — never vacuously green.
#
# FORMAT (typed OsbPin; parseable key = value; '#' comment; blanks ignored)
#   osb_tag         upstream OSB release tag the inheritance tracks.
#   osb_repo        upstream repo URL the tag is resolved against.
#   subtree_sha     content-SHA (40-hex) of the vendored vendor/osb/ subtree, OR
#                   the PENDING_NO_SUBTREE sentinel when nothing is vendored.
#                   validateOsbPin rejects any other value — a bump is never silent.
#   status          human-readable posture.
#   validation_ref  path to the governing brief / eval report.
#
# STATUS (2026-07-11): DORMANT — no vault-agnostic OSB libs are vendored under
#   vendor/osb/ yet (direction C: the patterns are inherited as emit-only
#   adapters, NOT a code subtree), so subtree_sha is the honest
#   PENDING_NO_SUBTREE sentinel. The live governance surface today is the shipped
#   *-source.ts extractors, which gate (a) scans for 0 write-surface violations.
#   A future real vendoring MUST record a real 40-hex subtree_sha here. Gates (b)
#   egress-leakage + (c) retrieval eval are DEFERRED (real I/O). Do NOT hand-edit
#   subtree_sha to a fabricated value — it is promoted only by a deliberate,
#   recorded vendoring.

osb_tag        = v0.11.1
osb_repo       = https://github.com/eugeniughelbur/obsidian-second-brain.git
subtree_sha    = PENDING_NO_SUBTREE
status         = dormant_no_subtree
validation_ref = docs/briefs/017-13.1-osb-anti-corruption-guard.md
